cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use superhuman, please cite it using these metadata."
title: "superhuman: an autonomous, closed-loop open-source contribution agent for Claude Code and Codex"
abstract: >-
  superhuman is a multi-agent harness that contributes merge-quality pull
  requests to real open-source projects. It picks an open issue, plans and
  writes the fix, scores its own pull request on a 10-dimension
  merge-probability rubric, iterates on the single weakest dimension, and
  repeats until a maintainer would merge it. Unlike open-loop coding agents
  that generate once, superhuman is closed-loop: it grades its own work before
  submission and calibrates a learned prior from every past merge outcome.
type: software
